The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Saturday, July 24, 2004 				 Telgi charges
																								New Delhi, July 23: The CBI has filed a chargesheet in Delhi against an associate of Abdul Karim Telgi, the alleged mastermind of the stamp paper scam, for the sale of fake stamps worth Rs 212 crore, reports our special correspondent.																								The case was initially registered by Delhi police in October 2002 and later transferred to the CBI, which named G. Vetrivel Sami alias Swami as an accused.																								Swami was appointed to open offices for the sale of fake stamps at Chandigarh and Ludhiana by Mohammad A. Hafiz, an associate of Telgi. Investigations revealed Swami would sell fake stamps to insurance companies and banks. The supplies would come from Hafiz in Delhi who got them from the Mumbai-based Telgi. 
